node.text:
Another American dream of mine came true today…my brand new frozen pizza line @hakkis donated —— pizzas to hungry brothers and sisters in NYC!!

It took years for me to make this project happen, I lost belief in myself sometimes along the way. But with amazing people supporting me I managed to get things done, and here I am doing my thing with the wonderful team members who believe in better tomorrow.

A portion of Hakki’s pizza goes to charities to end homelessness, which means YOU participate in this movement if you enjoy our delicious pizza! Check it out at your local NYC supermarket!!

We believe kindness is everything!
Be kind for no reason!

Special thanks to 
Mikey ferdi Wayne Leo erol serhat

I always wanted do something that I love which is to make pizza. It was never about making money to be rich. It was more about expressing my passion.
And that passion became more powerful when I started giving back! As always I say Be kind for no reason because kindness is free.

Same place same food same team Together with @pcny @nonstop_kreations  @intergalacticavatar this raining day we served 350 people today. It is always joyful to serve those who are hungry but cannot access to good food, and our commitment is even stronger throughout the pandemic. The smiles and nice words we received are PRICELESS!!!!

Meet your new favorite pizza, in a freezer near you!
As our corporation is growing day by day, it is important to keep our audience engaged with our latest news and item releases. Here is how our super tasty and delicious frozen pizza is made in our headquarters from start to finish. Enjoy.

Another American dream of mine came true today…my brand new frozen pizza line @hakkis donated —— pizzas to hungry brothers and sisters in NYC!!

It took years for me to make this project happen, I lost belief in myself sometimes along the way. But with amazing people supporting me I managed to get things done, and here I am doing my thing with the wonderful team members who believe in better tomorrow.

A portion of Hakki’s pizza goes to charities to end homelessness, which means YOU participate in this movement if you enjoy our delicious pizza! Check it out at your local NYC supermarket!!

We believe kindness is everything!
Be kind for no reason!

Special thanks to 
Mikey ferdi Wayne Leo erol serhat

node.text:
I started my day one in Lower East Side. Today it is my home and people here are my family. It was always my goal to support those who need food and shelter, the most essential things in life. This video makes me proud of me for not giving up my American dream!!

I really have to mention this.Lower East Side is home to me: I opened my first business here in 2010 and never forget that people here welcomed this immigrant pizza man. I have made so many good friends, some of whom I consider my family. Without their love and support I wouldn’t be who I am today.

I always wanted do something that I love which is to make pizza. It was never about making money to be rich. It was more about expressing my passion.
And that passion became more powerful when I started giving back!!

It is very fortunate for me to serve this community right now when tons of people need help like never before. It gives me a very special feeling to connect with amazing people here in my home to rebuild LES and give good energy!! 

Working with this amazing team I can’t thank them enough!🙏

I always wanted do something that I love which is to make pizza. It was never about making money to be rich. It was more about expressing my passion.
And that passion became more powerful when I started giving back! Be kind for no reason because kindness is free.

Same place same food same team Together with @pcny @nonstop_kreations we served 250 people today. It is always joyful to serve those who are hungry but cannot access to good food, and our commitment is even stronger throughout the pandemic. The smiles and nice words we received are PRICELESS!!!!

Böyle güzel bir oluşuma vesile olduğunuz için teşekkür ederim.

Her zaman birlik olup birbirimize yardım ettikçe daha güçlü olunacağına inanıyorum. 

Özellikle kadınların el emekleriyle katma değer oluşturup ekonomiye katkı sağlamaları çok değerli. Güçlü kadın, güçlü aile, güçlü toplum demek. Kadın emeği, güzel bir geleceğe de katkı sunuyor… Kadınlara bu konuda destek veren önlerini açan Eyüpsultan Belediyesi’ni ve Sayın Başkan @dnzkoken ‘i de tebrik ediyorum. 
Kadın umuttur, kadın yaşamdır... Bugünlere gelmem de en çok emeği olan, hayatta bana vazgeçmemeyi öğreten, her mücadelemde ilham kaynağım olan insan annemdir. 
Ben hiç durmadan çalışarak ve sürekli kendim üreterek hayatta bazı şeyleri başardım. Aynı şekilde şimdi burada da insanların kendi üretimleriyle hayatlarına ışık katmaları benim için çok anlamlı.

I really enjoy this project so much.

I always wanted do something that I love which is to make pizza. It was never about making money to be rich. It was more about expressing my passion.
And that passion became more powerful when I started giving back!!

It is very fortunate for me to serve this community right now when tons of people need help like never before. It gives me a very special feeling to connect with amazing people here in my home to rebuild and give good energy!! 

Working with this amazing team I can’t thank them enough! @4mycity.us @sudanosproduce @pcny @pcnyinthestreets_team 
it gives me everyday positive energy to support others in need.

Also it’s priceless to connect with others happy people with the same heart as me!

I want more people to experience the joy of giving.

You don’t need to be smart,
 you don’t need to be rich to help others with what you can do.

I want people to think that “If he can do it, I can do it too!” and I hope the community becomes better and better everyday. Because life’is to short
Whatever struggle you’re going thru it's only temporary. Being a good person is the biggest key to success

Only one thing is truly important to put God first and don’t  never even give up on your dreams.  #pizza4Good #livingthroughgiving

I really enjoy this project so much. Working with this amazing team I can’t thank them enough! @4mycity.us @sudanosproduce @pcny @pcnyinthestreets_team @abah9 
it gives me everyday positive energy to support others in need.

Also it’s priceless to connect with others happy people with the same heart as me!

I want more people to experience the joy of giving.

You don’t need to be smart,
 you don’t need to be rich to help others with what you can do.

I want people to think that “If he can do it, I can do it too!” and I hope the community becomes better and better everyday. Because life’is to short
Whatever struggle you’re going thru it's only temporary. Being a good person is the biggest key to success

Only one thing is truly important to put God first and don’t  never even give up on your dreams. #pizza4Good #livingthroughgiving
